exec --no-startup-id xset dpms 600

exec --no-startup-id xautolock -time 10 -locker i3lock

The above just _won't_ work for me. i3lock works with a keybinding but nothing seems to get xautolock working for me. 

I've tried other alternatives to xautolock (xss-lock-git, sinar) with no success either.

I'd love any tips, things to try.. anything to stop my brain from exploding!(and for my screen to lock)</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Oct 2014 08:38:20 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4768/xautolock-frustration/</guid></item><item><title>Comment by NimS for &lt;p&gt;from &lt;a href="https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/i3#Screensaver"&gt;https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;and&lt;/em&gt;power_management (Archlinux)&lt;/p&gt;

